Shirakawa Says Yen Gaining Because of Rising Global Uncertainty

-- B y   A k i   I t o
-- 
2011-09-22T17:35:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-22/shirakawa-says-yen-gaining-because-of-rising-global-uncertainty.html
Bank of Japan (8301)  Governor Masaaki
Shirakawa said the yen has been gaining in value because of
rising uncertainty about the outlook for the global economy.  Shirakawa said today policy makers should make efforts to
reduce uncertainty, without elaborating on what steps he
believes should be taken. He spoke to reporters in  Washington .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aki Ito in Tokyo at 
 aito16@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
